<p>Problem: you have a good month and then a bad month.  You put all the effort into getting clients and then drop everything to get into candidate sourcing mode. Bad month follows well. Stress ensues and the cycle repeats.</p>
<p>This lack of predictable means we take bad decisions. We get back to our old ways of hitting the phones and email/LinkedIn blasts. Then the cycle begins again.</p>
<p>Want to get off this hamster wheel?  End the famine and Feast on this!</p>
<p>Andy Whitehead</p>
